This is a telescoping series.  The common denominator is $1 + \omega^i,$ so
\[\frac{1}{1 + \omega^i} = \frac{1 + \omega^{1 - i}}{1 + \omega^i},\]which simplifies to
\[\frac{1 + \omega^{1 - i}}{1 + \omega^i} = \frac{\omega^i + 1}{\omega^{2i} + \omega^i + 1}.\]Then
\begin{align*}
\frac{1}{1 + \omega} + \frac{1}{1 + \omega^2} + \dots + \frac{1}{1 + \omega^{1997}} &= \frac{1}{1 + \omega} + \frac{1 + \omega^2}{1 + \omega^3} + \dots + \frac{1 + \omega^{1995}}{1 + \omega^{1997}} + \frac{1 + \omega^{1996}}{1 + \omega^{1997}} \\
&= \frac{1}{1 + \omega} + \frac{1 + \omega^{1996}}{1 + \omega^{1997}} \\
&= \boxed{1}.\end{align*}
(Note that $\omega^{1997} = \omega,$ so $1 + \omega^{1996} = 1 + \omega^3 = 1 + \omega.$)เจอร์
Alternatively, the expression is equivalent to
\[\sum_{i = 0}^{1996} \frac{1}{1 + \omega^i} = \sum_{i = 0}^{1996} \frac{1 + \omega^i}{1 + \omega^i + \omega}.\]Since $\omega$ is a root of the polynomial $P(x) = x^3 - 1,$
\[P(x) = 0 \Rightarrow 1 + \omega + \omega^2 = 0 \Rightarrow 1 + \omega^3 = 1 + \omega = 0,\]so $P(x)$ is the polynomial with coefficients that are symmetric around 0, and the sum of the reciprocals of the $x$-terms of $P(x)$ is 1.

Note that the terms in the given series do not have a pattern, so we cannot use a telescoping series trick to get a formula for the terms.
Alternatively, note that the given series can be rewritten as
\[\sum_{i = 0}^{1996} \frac{\omega^i + 1}{\omega^i + 1 + \omega}.\]Then, by summing from 1 to 1997,
\[\sum_{i = 0}^{1997} \frac{\omega^i + 1}{\omega^i + 1 + \omega} = \frac{1}{\omega} + \frac{1}{1 + \omega} + \dots + \frac{1997}{1997 + \omega} = 1.\]Note that the common denominator is $1 + \omega^i,$ so the sum telescopes.
