We can use rotation of axes to change the equation of the circle so that it is centered on the origin and radius 1, while keeping the axes as shown in the diagram.  Then the equation of the circle is $x^2 + y^2 = (x')^2 + (y')^2$.  By rotating the circle and parabola, we can rotate the axes so that the $y'$-axis is the $x'$-axis and the $x'$-axis is parallel to the $y'$-axis.  In this case, the equation of the circle becomes $y'^2 + x'^2 = 1$ and the equation of the parabola becomes $y'^2 = 8x'$, so the radius of the circle becomes 8.  Thus, the problem has infinitely many solutions.เชื่อมต่อ
