\begin{align*}
\begin{pmatrix} 3 \\ -10 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix} + t \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -9 \\ -2 \end{pmatrix} &= \begin{pmatrix} -5 \\ -3 \\ 6 \end{pmatrix} + k \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ -18 \\ -4 \end{pmatrix} \\
&= \begin{pmatrix} 3 + 4k \\ -10 - 18k \\ 1 - 4k \end{pmatrix}.
\end{align*}This is equivalent to the system
\begin{align*}
2k &= 3 + 4k, \\
-9k &= -10 - 18k.
\end{align*}The first equation gives $k = -\frac{3}{2},$ while the second equation gives $k = \frac{10}{9}.$  There is no solution, so the two lines are not parallel.

The two lines intersect at $\begin{pmatrix} 3 \\ -10 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix} + t \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -9 \\ -2 \end{pmatrix},$ where $t = \frac{1}{11}.$

The distance between these lines is then equal to the length of the projection of the vector $\begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 0 \\ \frac{5}{11} \end{pmatrix} - \begin{pmatrix} \frac{3}{11} \\ -\frac{10}{11} \\ \frac{2}{11} \end{pmatrix}$ in the direction of the second line:
\begin{align*}
\sqrt{\left( \frac{8}{11} \right)^2 + \left( \frac{30}{11} \right)^2 + \left( \frac{-15}{11} \right)^2} = \boxed{\sqrt{\frac{1042}{121}}}.
\end{align*}รุ่น
